text:
Jonathan Cantwell (8 January 1982 – 6 November 2018) was an Australian professional road bicycle racer. He formerly rode for UCI Professional Continental Team. Cantwell made his Grand Tour début at the 2012 Tour de France. Cantwell took his first top ten placing on stage 4, when he finished sixth on the stage.
Cantwell died on 6 November 2018 at the age of 36.
